parameters: GabText I've not noticed it before, but this mansion is quite big.
GabText Compared to our agency, that is.
GabText Noian 101: There's no problems one cannot solve with money.
GabText But usually, the problem is the lack of it.
GabText Haah... And none of the sorcery stuff worked in Noian.
GabText Well, Monto's Enchanted items could work...
GabText So why don't you ask him for some valuables?
GabText I mean, Alchemy Enchant is pretty basic for him.
GabText Then, you can take his item and sell it in Noian for money.
GabText Vivian! The fact you can't be harmed by common Noian guns...
GabText Does still mean I can be shot to death!
GabText What if robbers break in our agency and demands money..
GabText Just because we suddenly become rich?
Then there's no point of getting rich in the first place.
GabText (Wait, just that? Not "But I can protect you?")
\MaidDear Guest, there're still time before dinner.
If you want to speak with Master, He should be in his room.
He didn't lock the door, so just knock and go in.
\MaidDear Guest, since it's the first time this mansion has gathered so many people for a dinner...
\MaidWe're now very busy doing our chores.
\ChrisI'd say I don't see the mess you're talking about.
\MaidIs that so? Then our master would claim no responsibility if you fall in the Storage Room and hurt yourself.
